  <p>I just double checked in Gutsy, as I was running 8.04.  Works fine.  I'm using gVim.  If you use vim in the shell, then you need to setup your shell colors, as there is nothing a color scheme can do to change them (the appropriate colors are in the comments of the color scheme).</p>

<p>Make sure your vimrc settings are correct:
<br />set background=dark 
<br />syntax on
<br />colorscheme ir_black</p>

