          <li class="alt"><a name="comment_128"> </a>
  <div class="commentname_admin">
    <span class="commentmeta">&nbsp;October 22, 2008 09:02</span>
      <a href='http://blog.infinitered.com' rel='external nofollow'>Todd Werth</a>
  </div>

  <div class='commenttext-admin'>
  <p>Greg,</p>

<p>Folders that start with a dot (.vim) are hidden.  Or you simply don't have a .vim folder.  If you don't have one, then you can simply create it.</p>

<p>If you're unfamiliar with opening hidden folders, here are two ways (this is for OS X as I see from your site that you use OS X):
<br />* Open it in Finder using Terminal:  open ~/.vim
<br />* Or open it in Finder using the menu: Menu/Go/Go To Folder, then just type ~/.vim</p>
</div>   
