          <li class="alt"><a name="comment_224"> </a>
  <div class="commentname">
      Antti
    <span class="commentmeta">October 09, 2009 12:57&nbsp;</span>
  </div>

  <div class='commenttext'>
  <p>A beautiful scheme!</p>

<p>I found some things less than perfect for my use and did some modifications for myself:</p>

<p>Type (#ffffb8) didn't stand out enough from white text, so I made it more yellow:</p>

<p>hi Type guifg=#FFFF98 guibg=NONE gui=NONE ctermfg=yellow ctermbg=NONE cterm=NONE</p>

<p>I use 'list' to show tab characters, so SpecialKey with nonblack background stood out too much:</p>

<p>hi SpecialKey guifg=#808080 guibg=#000000 gui=NONE ctermfg=NONE ctermbg=NONE cterm=NONE</p>

<p>Finally, I didn't like the black text non-current status windows and made the background a bit lighter as well:</p>

<p>hi VertSplit guifg=#202020 guibg=#404040 gui=NONE ctermfg=darkgray ctermbg=darkgray cterm=NONE
<br />hi StatusLine guifg=#dddddd guibg=#404040 gui=italic ctermfg=white ctermbg=darkgray cterm=NONE
<br />hi StatusLineNC guifg=#777777 guibg=#404040 gui=NONE ctermfg=blue ctermbg=darkgray cterm=NONE </p>

<p>With this modifications, I'm happier than ever. Thanks for sharing!
</p>
</div>   
