    <span class="commentmeta">November 10, 2010 07:38&nbsp;</span>
  </div>

  <div class='commenttext'>
  <p>al.jes,  </p>

<p>~ is your home folder.  And any folder or file that begins with a . is hidden.  So you need to create the .vim folder in your home folder.  The problem is you won't be able to create it using finder.  You can in the console (Terminal in Utilities) like so: 
<br />mkdir ~/.vim</p>

<p>And you can open it in finder, using the console like so:
<br />open ~/.vim</p>
</div>   
</li>
          <li class="alt"><a name="comment_309"> </a>
  <div class="commentname">
      <a href='http://al.jes.free.fr' rel='external nofollow'>al.jes</a>
    <span class="commentmeta">November 11, 2010 21:58&nbsp;</span>
  </div>

  <div class='commenttext'>
  <p>Thank you !</p>
</div>   
